### Motivation

- Provide a local read-only tool to scan Ren'Py projects for structure, assets and Git status and to edit/export Dialogue blocks without modifying the target project.
- Ship a self-contained developer experience (backend API + native static frontend) to interactively inspect projects and manage generated dialogue exports.

### Description

- Add a FastAPI backend (`backend/app.py`) with endpoints to open/scan projects, list assets, read Git status, and manage Dialogue block documents and export (`/api/project/open`, `/api/assets/list`, `/api/git/status`, `/api/dialogue/*`).
- Introduce Pydantic models (`backend/models.py`) and read-only helpers: project scanner (`backend/project_scanner.py`), asset scanner (`backend/asset_scanner.py`), and Git status reader (`backend/git_status.py`).
- Implement Dialogue document read/save/validate/export logic in `backend/dialogue_manager.py` that persists `tools_data/dialogue_blocks.json` and writes `game/generated_dialogue_blocks.rpy` when exporting.
- Add a native static frontend (`frontend/index.html`, `frontend/app.js`, `frontend/style.css`) to drive the API, plus dev scripts (`scripts/*.ps1`), `requirements.txt`, `.gitignore`, and an expanded `README.md` documenting usage and safety boundaries.

### Testing

- Ran Python compilation check: `python -m compileall backend`, which completed successfully.
- Validated frontend JS syntax with `node --check frontend/app.js`, which passed without errors.
- Performed git whitespace check with `git diff --check`, which reported no issues.
